From 33dae398de7c7390ba295d44f4c93b5954221e75 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 9 Mar 2020 19:15:04 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] net: tg3: reject unsupported coalescing params
Git-commit: 3eb2efbea193789397c36f52b17d8692ac79bf68
Patch-mainline: v5.7-rc1
References: jsc#SLE-14859

Set ethtool_ops->supported_coalesce_params to let
the core reject unsupported coalescing parameters.

This driver did not previously reject unsupported parameters.

Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kuba@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Michael Chan <michael.chan@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Denis Kirjanov <denis.kirjanov@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/tg3.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/tg3.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/tg3.c
index 10a7959d5496..45e88691a88e 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/tg3.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/broadcom/tg3.c
@@ -14171,6 +14171,11 @@ static int tg3_get_eee(struct net_device *dev, struct ethtool_eee *edata)
 }
 
 static const struct ethtool_ops tg3_ethtool_ops = {
+	.supported_coalesce_params = ETHTOOL_COALESCE_USECS |
+				     ETHTOOL_COALESCE_MAX_FRAMES |
+				     ETHTOOL_COALESCE_USECS_IRQ |
+				     ETHTOOL_COALESCE_MAX_FRAMES_IRQ |
+				     ETHTOOL_COALESCE_STATS_BLOCK_USECS,
 	.get_drvinfo		= tg3_get_drvinfo,
 	.get_regs_len		= tg3_get_regs_len,
 	.get_regs		= tg3_get_regs,
